1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Special Olympics Louisiana for providing athletic programs for children and
3 adults.
4 WHEREAS, it is with great pride that the Legislature of Louisiana recognizes
5 Special Olympics Louisiana for its ongoing efforts to provide children and adults with
6 opportunities to compete in athletic events and develop physical fitness; and
7 WHEREAS, Special Olympics Louisiana provides year-round sports training and
8 athletic competition in a variety of Olympic-type sports for children and adults with
9 intellectual disabilities; and
10 WHEREAS, the mission of Special Olympics Louisiana is to give individuals with
11 intellectual disabilities continuing opportunities to develop physical fitness, demonstrate
12 courage, experience joy, and participate in a sharing of gifts, skills, and friendship with their
13 families, fellow Special Olympic athletes, and the community; and
14 WHEREAS, the Special Olympics Unified Champion Schools program is aimed at
15 promoting social inclusion through intentionally planned and implemented activities that
16 affect systems-wide change; the goals of the program include providing students with and
17 without intellectual disabilities with meaningful unified sports opportunities and inclusive
18 youth leadership opportunities and increasing awareness and education activities that
19 promote inclusion and engage all students in creating a socially-inclusive school climate;
